subSubSection.paragraph:
A second remark concerns the anterior paranuchal plate versus the marginal plate. Traditionally, the marginal plate is defined in arthrodires as the skull component bearing the main lateral sensory line groove and the postmarginal sensory line groove (
Goujet 1984a: 102
).

This canal is not observable or present on that plate in some other Saudi specimens (MNHN.F.1992-6-132 and135; 
Figs 2C, D
; 
3A, B
). Thus, the identification as a “marginal plate” is not obvious. Additionally, it contacts medially the medial paranuchal plate and the posterior paranuchal plate posteriorly. Therefore it belongs to the paranuchal complex and may also correspond to the anterior paranuchal plate. It also bears the confluence between the main sensory line groove and the posterior part of the posterior pit line, a characteristic for a paranuchal plate.
